{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 7 illustrates the three cases in Proposition 7.",
    "The gure plots the long-run growth rate of wages as a function of the rate of automation.",
    "If λg is suciently low as in case 1, then the wage growth rate is increasing in the rate of automation as the upward-sloping part of the curve indicates.",
    "Once λg surpasses the rst threshold value, the growth rate of wages starts to decline as λg increases further.",
    "Lastly, if λg surpasses the second threshold value, then wages do not grow in the long run and stay at A."
  ]
}